The paper discusses the computational power of modern neural network architectures, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with neural networks. "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the capacity of neural networks to learn and process data. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the computational power of AI models. "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) and "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the properties of architectures used for processing input sequences, which is relevant to natural language processing and computer vision.
